    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Pomona’s early settlers arrived in the early 1700s, farming the fertile soils of what would become Rockland County.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Pomona,_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The village straddles two towns—Ramapo and Haverstraw—making it one of the few New York villages split between jurisdictions.",
